  "text": "The second important study in elucidating DON binding features is the one which solved the three dimensional structure of Fusarium graminearum Tri101 enzyme with DON bound into the enzyme's active pocket [CITATION_1] . In this study, Garvey et al. highlighted the major residues involved in DON caging and catalysis. Furthermore, the team underlined a major sequence motif that is involved in Tri101 functionality, namely the 156HXXXD160 motif. Surprisingly, the same motif can be identified within the DON-affinity binders near their C-termini (Figure 3b with gray highlight) .",
